definitions.definition: The short month following January and preceding March in the Roman , Julian , and Gregorian calendars , used in all three calendars for intercalation or addition of leap days .
A female given name transferred from the month name [in turn from English] .

main_definition: The short month following January and preceding March in the Roman , Julian , and Gregorian calendars , used in all three calendars for intercalation or addition of leap days .
